In this experiment, you will have to remember some briefly presented colors and lines.
You will need to complete #X# trials, each of which takes around 5 seconds, and the entire experiment should take less than #X# minutes total. 
There are no scheduled breaks in the experiment, but feel free to take breaks between trials, as the trial does not begin until you click a central fixation point. 
Finally, please do not participant if you do not have normal or corrected-to-normal color vision.

Before each trial starts, there will be four placeholder circles. 
Once you click on the central cross to start each trial, two of these four circles will be filled with colors of various shades, or lines of various orientations, or a combination of shades and orientations. 
Shortly after, the two items in these two circles will dissapear, and two new items will appear in the other two circles. 

In this example, the two circles on the left are first filled by one color and one orientation. Then, the two circles on the right are also filled by one color and one orientation. 
